{"id":35734,"date":"2021-04-22T12:40:21","date_gmt":"2021-04-22T08:40:21","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=35734"},"modified":"2021-04-22T12:45:06","modified_gmt":"2021-04-22T08:45:06","slug":"wudu-3-times","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/22\/wudu-3-times\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Wudu: Washing limbs three times in ablution"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Amr reported: A man came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how does one perform purification?\u201d The Prophet called for a vessel of water, then he washed his hands three times, then he washed his face three times, then he washed his arms to the elbow three times, then he wiped his head, then he put his fingers around his earlobes, wiping the back with his thumbs and the interior with his index fingers, then he washed his feet three times, each three by three. Then, the Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Such is the ablution. Whoever adds to this has sinned and done wrong.<\/strong>&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 135<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih li ghayrihi<\/em><\/strong> (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064d\u0648 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064b\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u